It also mentions obtaining competitive results on the VOC 2012 segmentation benchmark, which is a well-known benchmark dataset in computer vision. 

The paper also involves the use of convolutional networks, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. 

Additionally, the paper mentions the use of self-supervision, which is a technique commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. 

Therefore, the 5 likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM, ordered from most to least likely.
